#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:5
msgid "Add-ons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:7
msgid ""
"Scrapy's add-on system is a framework which unifies managing and configuring "
"components that extend Scrapy's core functionality, such as middlewares, "
"extensions, or pipelines. It provides users with a plug-and-play experience "
"in Scrapy extension management, and grants extensive configuration control "
"to developers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:15
msgid "Activating and configuring add-ons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:17
msgid ""
"During :class:`~scrapy.crawler.Crawler` initialization, the list of enabled "
"add-ons is read from your ``ADDONS`` setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:20
msgid ""
"The ``ADDONS`` setting is a dict in which every key is an add-on class or "
"its import path and the value is its priority."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:23
msgid ""
"This is an example where two add-ons are enabled in a project's ``settings."
"py``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:26
msgid ""
"ADDONS = {\n"
"    'path.to.someaddon': 0,\n"
"    SomeAddonClass: 1,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:33
msgid "Writing your own add-ons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:35
msgid ""
"Add-ons are :ref:`components <topics-components>` that include one or both "
"of the following methods:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:40
msgid ""
"This method is called during the initialization of the :class:`~scrapy."
"crawler.Crawler`. Here, you should perform dependency checks (e.g. for "
"external Python libraries) and update the :class:`~scrapy.settings.Settings` "
"object as wished, e.g. enable components for this add-on or set required "
"configuration of other extensions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr "參數"

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:46 ../../../topics/addons.rst:55
msgid "The settings object storing Scrapy/component configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:51
msgid ""
"Use this class method instead of the :meth:`update_settings` method to "
"update :ref:`pre-crawler settings <pre-crawler-settings>` whose value is "
"used before the :class:`~scrapy.crawler.Crawler` object is created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:58
msgid ""
"The settings set by the add-on should use the ``addon`` priority (see :ref:"
"`populating-settings` and :func:`scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.set`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:61
msgid ""
"class MyAddon:\n"
"    def update_settings(self, settings):\n"
"        settings.set(\"DNSCACHE_ENABLED\", True, \"addon\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:65
msgid ""
"This allows users to override these settings in the project or spider "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:68
msgid ""
"When editing the value of a setting instead of overriding it entirely, it is "
"usually best to leave its priority unchanged. For example, when editing a :"
"ref:`component priority dictionary <component-priority-dictionaries>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:72
msgid ""
"If the ``update_settings`` method raises :exc:`scrapy.exceptions."
"NotConfigured`, the add-on will be skipped. This makes it easy to enable an "
"add-on only when some conditions are met."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:77
msgid "Fallbacks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:79
msgid ""
"Some components provided by add-ons need to fall back to \"default\" "
"implementations, e.g. a custom download handler needs to send the request "
"that it doesn't handle via the default download handler, or a stats "
"collector that includes some additional processing but otherwise uses the "
"default stats collector. And it's possible that a project needs to use "
"several custom components of the same type, e.g. two custom download "
"handlers that support different kinds of custom requests and still need to "
"use the default download handler for other requests. To make such use cases "
"easier to configure, we recommend that such custom components should be "
"written in the following way:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:89
msgid ""
"The custom component (e.g. ``MyDownloadHandler``) shouldn't inherit from the "
"default Scrapy one (e.g. ``scrapy.core.downloader.handlers.http11."
"HTTP11DownloadHandler``), but instead be able to load the class of the "
"fallback component from a special setting (e.g. "
"``MY_FALLBACK_DOWNLOAD_HANDLER``), create an instance of it and use it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:95
msgid ""
"The add-ons that include these components should read the current value of "
"the default setting (e.g. ``DOWNLOAD_HANDLERS``) in their "
"``update_settings()`` methods, save that value into the fallback setting "
"(``MY_FALLBACK_DOWNLOAD_HANDLER`` mentioned earlier) and set the default "
"setting to the component provided by the add-on (e.g. "
"``MyDownloadHandler``). If the fallback setting is already set by the user, "
"they shouldn't change it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:102
msgid ""
"This way, if there are several add-ons that want to modify the same setting, "
"all of them will fallback to the component from the previous one and then to "
"the Scrapy default. The order of that depends on the priority order in the "
"``ADDONS`` setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:109
msgid "Add-on examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:111
msgid "Set some basic configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:114
msgid ""
"from myproject.pipelines import MyPipeline\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class MyAddon:\n"
"    def update_settings(self, settings):\n"
"        settings.set(\"DNSCACHE_ENABLED\", True, \"addon\")\n"
"        settings.remove_from_list(\"METAREFRESH_IGNORE_TAGS\", "
"\"noscript\")\n"
"        settings.setdefault_in_component_priority_dict(\n"
"            \"ITEM_PIPELINES\", MyPipeline, 200\n"
"        )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:129
msgid ""
"When editing a :ref:`component priority dictionary <component-priority-"
"dictionaries>` setting, like :setting:`ITEM_PIPELINES`, consider using "
"setting methods like :meth:`~scrapy.settings.BaseSettings."
"replace_in_component_priority_dict`, :meth:`~scrapy.settings.BaseSettings."
"set_in_component_priority_dict` and :meth:`~scrapy.settings.BaseSettings."
"setdefault_in_component_priority_dict` to avoid mistakes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:138
msgid "Check dependencies:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:140
msgid ""
"class MyAddon:\n"
"    def update_settings(self, settings):\n"
"        try:\n"
"            import boto\n"
"        except ImportError:\n"
"            raise NotConfigured(\"MyAddon requires the boto library\")\n"
"        ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:150
msgid "Access the crawler instance:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:152
msgid ""
"class MyAddon:\n"
"    def __init__(self, crawler) -> None:\n"
"        super().__init__()\n"
"        self.crawler = crawler\n"
"\n"
"    @classmethod\n"
"    def from_crawler(cls, crawler):\n"
"        return cls(crawler)\n"
"\n"
"    def update_settings(self, settings): ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:165
msgid "Use a fallback component:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/addons.rst:167
msgid ""
"from scrapy.utils.misc import build_from_crawler\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"FALLBACK_SETTING = \"MY_FALLBACK_DOWNLOAD_HANDLER\"\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class MyHandler:\n"
"    lazy = False\n"
"\n"
"    def __init__(self, crawler):\n"
"        dhcls = load_object(crawler.settings.get(FALLBACK_SETTING))\n"
"        self._fallback_handler = build_from_crawler(dhcls, crawler)\n"
"\n"
"    async def download_request(self, request):\n"
"        if request.meta.get(\"my_params\"):\n"
"            # handle the request\n"
"            ...\n"
"        else:\n"
"            return await self._fallback_handler.download_request(request)\n"
"\n"
"    async def close(self):\n"
"        pass\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class MyAddon:\n"
"    def update_settings(self, settings):\n"
"        if not settings.get(FALLBACK_SETTING):\n"
"            settings.set(\n"
"                FALLBACK_SETTING,\n"
"                settings.getwithbase(\"DOWNLOAD_HANDLERS\")[\"https\"],\n"
"                \"addon\",\n"
"            )\n"
"        settings[\"DOWNLOAD_HANDLERS\"][\"https\"] = MyHandler"
msgstr ""
